                        "name": "nico",
                        "displayName": "Nico Edtinger",
                        "active": true
                    },
                    "body": "Could you first explain the bug in the APOP handling?\n\nSending the password in clear text should be avoided if possible and therefor APOP should be used if the server signals its support. We still fallback to USER\/PASS if the server sends a timestamp in the greeting but has problems with the APOP command.\n\nI fail to see the use of an option to make it more insecure. Especially as you already have that option, as you can extend the POP3 class.",
